<DOC><DOCNO> AP890602-0261 </DOCNO><FILEID>AP-NR-06-02-89 1527EST</FILEID><FIRST>u f PM-WallStreet3pm     06-02 0372</FIRST><SECOND>PM-Wall Street 3pm,0389</SECOND><DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE><TEXT>   The stock market advanced broadly today,responding to employment statistics that raised hopes for an easierFederal Reserve credit policy and lower interest rates.   The Dow Jones average of 30 industrials rose 20.03 to 2,510.66by 3 p.m. on Wall Street, surpassing the post-crash closing high of2,502.02 it reached on May 22.   Gainers outnumbered losers by more than 2 to 1 in nationwidetrading of New York Stock Exchange-listed issues, with 1,080 up,463 down and 436 unchanged.   The Labor Department reported that nonfarm payroll employmentincreased by 101,000 in May _ only about half of the amountprojected by economists at leading brokerage firms.   Janet Norwood, commissioner of the Bureau of Labor Statistics,described job growth as ``very slow.''   Traders seized on the data as evidence that the Federal Reservemight soon relax its credit policy, seeking to cushion the economyagainst the risks of a recession.   Interest rates dropped sharply in the credit markets. Prices oflong-term government bonds, which move in the opposite directionfrom interest rates, rose more than $10 for each $1,000 in facevalue, putting their yields in the neighborhood of 8.5 percent.   Texaco led the active list, up } at 49}. The stock fell 2\points Thursday as financier Carl Icahn unloaded his holdings ofmore than 42 million Texaco shares.   USX, meanwhile, slipped back } to 36} after taking a 2]-pointjump Thursday. News of the Texaco transaction prompted speculationthat Icahn might be preparing a deal for USX, in which he also haslong held a large stake.   Amgen climbed 3~ to 44~ in the over-the-counter market. OnThursday the Food and Drug Administration gave Amgen approval toproduce and sell a genetically engineered drug for treatment ofanemia in kidney patients.   Sun Microsystems, another OTC issue, fell 1\ to 19{. The companysaid it expects to report a significant decline in earnings for thefiscal quarter ending June 30.   The NYSE's composite index of all its listed common stocksgained 1.52 to 181.15. At the American Stock Exchange, the marketvalue index was up 1.50 at 359.59.   Volume on the Big Board came to 191.30 million shares with anhour to go.</TEXT></DOC>